    "Style-GAN [39] borrowed from the style transfer literature and proposed a different generator architecture for adversarial neural networks with learning.",
    "Intuitive, scale-specific control of the synthesis is provided by the innovative architecture, which also results in an unsupervised, automatically learned separation of high-level information (such as stance and identity when trained on human faces) and random variance in the resulting pictures (such as freckles, hair).",
    "Self-supervised GAN [40] made by Tran et al.",
    "Self-supervised (SS) tasks have been proposed as a solution to the catastrophe fading problem in the GAN discriminator.",
    "They find SS task issues that let a generator with a lot of mode collapse work well."
